Deji Elumoye in Abuja President Muhammadu Buhari has felicitated the first Nigerian to bag a doctorate in Energy and Environment, Dr Yunus Abiodun Akintunde, as he marks his 60th birthday anniversary on March 6, 2022.The president, in a release issued on Saturday by his Media Adviser, Femi Adesina, hailed the service of the celebrant to his native Oyo State, to Nigeria, and to scholarship, through his current book, ‘Dimensions of Energy Poverty and Rural Electrification in Nigeria’.He rejoiced with the family, friends and associates of Dr Akintunde, sharing the joy of the auspicious celebration with them.Akintunde has a rich network of friends round the country, making him a detribalized Nigerian, a fact the president applauded and recommended to all and sundry.He wished the celebrant long life, prosperity and further service to motherland Nigeria.